The Network Time Protocol (NTP) is [[Article description::used to synchronize the [[system time]] with other devices over the network.]] This usually happens in a client-server model.

== Implementations ==

In Gentoo, several implementations of the Network Time Protocol can be used:

* [[ntp]]
* [[openntpd]]
* [[chrony]]
* {{Package|net-misc/ntpsec}}

== Alternatives ==

* {{package|net-misc/tlsdate}} - Update local time over HTTPS

